work administration end user support  equipment management  monitoring ninstructional and service labs  computer  video  etc   translation  routine support for publications n record keeping  writing copy for university or department newsletters or non research publications  correspondence  etc   advising providing curricular and academic advice to students  providing support nto advisors   and outreach duties  recruiting students  publicizing programs and activities to campus and npublic constituencies  and working with assisting with event management Research Assistants  For tax purposes  research activities may include  but are not limited to  the following examples of applying and mastering research concepts  practices  or methods of scholarship   conducting experiments  organizing or analyzing data  presenting findings  collaborating with others in preparing publications  and conducting institutional research for an academic or administrative unit Teaching Assistants  Duties include  but are not limited to  duties primarily in support of instruction and educational services such as   leading discussion sections  leading class discussions  holding lectures  the design of course materials  exam preparation  proctoring and grading assignments or exams  holding office hours  note taking  meeting special needs of students with disabilities  and or any other educational activity or service provided    Advertising While many colleges may post internally  units may also post openings via the Hiretouch system and have their vacancy posted on the UIC HR website under Career Opportunites Career Opportunites Eligibility Requirement The registration requirement for a student to hold a graduate assistantship is at least eight     hours each semester Union Graduate Assistants with a title of Graduate Assistant or Grad Teaching Assistant and have a total FTE between   % and   % are covered by the  GEO Contract  GEO Contract Offer letter Templates Hiring units must follow the assistantship offer letter templates available on the UIC HR website for Teaching Assistants and Graduate Assistants that are covered by the GEO contract   There are also recommended template letters  available for graduate research assistants and graduate hourly appointments  n template letters  Tuition Waiver Tuition  excluding differentials    Selected Fee Waiver Eligibility  Must meet registration requirements throughout the term and hold an assistantship between   % and   % for a minimum of    continuous calendar days during the period beginning a week before instruction and the last day of finals during Fall or Spring semester and for    continuous calendar days during the summer term service period  A   %   % time appointment must be maintained for the duration of the assistantship to be eligible for a tuition and selected fee waiver  Increasing the assistantship above   % or decreasing it below   % will cause loss of the waiver  The only exceptions are appointments during the break between Fall and Spring semesters  as well as during the Spring break Fall Semester                                Last day of finals Example of    day appts              Spring Semester        n                         Week before instruction begins               Last day of finals Example of    day appts                                                  Summer Term                                 Service Dates Example of    day appts                           n                                    More detailed information regarding Graduate Assistantships can be found on the  Graduate College website   Graduate College website  Tuition waivers will cover the cost of the full tuition except for those graduate programs that have tuition differentials  Please see  Admission and Records  for a current listing of Tuition and Fees breakdown  n  Admission and Records  Note  Those who received an assistantship tuition waiver in the Spring semester  but do not have an assistantship in the summer  will be eligible for the summer auto waiver  A student with a summer assistantship must meet the criteria for a summer waiver regardless of whether or not they held a Spring appointment Taxability of Certain Assistantship Tuition and Service Fee Waivers  In compliance with Internal Revenue Code Section             per calendar year in tuition and service fee waivers associated with GA and or PGA appointments is excluded from taxable income  Please see the University Payroll and Benefits website  for more information  n University Payroll and Benefits website Pre doctoral fellowships  tGraduate students may also hold Pre doctoral Fellowships which are zero percent  non benefit eligible appointments awarded to Graduate students  who have yet to earn their Doctorate or terminal degree  n  nMinima for Graduate Appointments n Minima for Graduate Appointments Working at UIC      Graduate Assistants Grad Assistant Dental and Vision Benefits   Graduate College Graduate Minima  Taxability of Certain Tuition and Service Fee Waivers    Minima for Graduate Appointments Graduate Assistantships and Graduate Hourly HR Front End Transaction   Graduate Reappointment HR Front End   Reading the Audit Trail Processing Jobs For Graduate Appointments Processing Summer Jobs GA New Hire Checklist        Appointment Process for Graduate Assistants        Other Temporary Academic Appointments IRS Publication     Tax Benefits for Education Quick Links Benefits Benefits Orientation Registration Charitable Giving at UIC Employee Performance Review NESSIE Office of Access and Equity Office of International Services Office of Business and Financial Services Payroll Schedules Form W   U of I Alumni Association UIC Time Off and Leaves Employee Exit Checklist  Schedule of Approved Holidays for UIC Fiscal Year      P T Deadlines  PDF Faculty Affairs Website Faculty Handbook Faculty Scholarship Support Faculty Senate Faculty Policies  Procedures  Guidelines Faculty Recognition New Faculty Orient